cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CE 

The paper involves the development and application of a deep learning-based surrogate model for predicting dynamic subsurface flow in channelized geological models. This involves the use of deep convolutional and recurrent neural network architectures, specifically a residual U-Net and a convolutional long short term memory recurrent network. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science)
